<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-57-0779 </DOCNO><TEXT>Conditions for exact quantum scattering problem transition into an adiabaticallylimited case are investigated. Different types of long-living statesare considered. It is shown that characteristic scattering time obtainedfrom adiabaticity condition, is not directly connected with quantum timeof flight, and the difference between these two parameters can be sufficientenough.</TEXT></DOC>